node.text: Yes guys anothet German cat review. If you don't like it get, get over it lol. node.text:
LOOKS LIKE A MODEL!! - Another Banger Up!  Be sure to DM @americanmusclehd or @classicsdaily for more details. 
_
‘34 Ford LSX 454 $230k appraisal. Asking 92k #hotrod #Ford #pickup #lsx454

Powertrain/Drivetrain Type and Modifications:
The engine is a 627 hp Chevrolet performance LSX454 backed by their 4l85e transmission. Inglese Fuel injection controlled by F.A.S.T. electronics feeds the engine through custom made intake manifolds. We custom made engine mounts, vacuum chambered valley pan, and one off headers that have removable baffles and an internal flange design for the turn out. The Vintage Air front runner is custom coated to match the rest of the drive train and suspension which is cerakote ceramic coatings. Faux distributor doubles as a oil fill.

Chassis Type and Modifications:
It features a custom built chassis by Roadstershop with 4 wheel independent Kugel Components suspension and a Winters quick change rear end. Huge Wilwood Disc Brakes have been adapted with 6 piston calipers on all 4 corners. All of the suspension is cerakote ceramic coatings. We custom made backing plates, sway bars, shock brace, as well as custom dual gas tanks that also double as a partial belly pan. Schott wheels wrapped in Nitto tires to get the power to the ground. The frame has been completely bodyworked and painted and everything is painted, polished, or chromed.

Exterior Modifications:
The body, which is finished in Sherwin Williams Khaos Red, has been endlessly modified to achieve clean lines with tons of details. The roof has been chopped 3 1/2, custom floor channeled the body 3", The rear window was raise 1" and widened 7 1/2", cowl vent was filled, the hinges were redone so the hinge pin threads in from the bottom, the lower cowl was curved the match the reveal in the 32 style rails. The rear of the cab was 90% replaced and made from scratch, the rear insert of the cab is remade to follow the curvature of the body lines, the fire wall was made from scratch and moved out 1” to add foot room. It was also installed at 3 degrees to match the angle of the cylinder head.
